Class CarEntity

java.lang.Object
com.app.persistence.entity.BaseEntity
com.app.persistence.entity.CarEntity
@Entity public class CarEntity extends BaseEntity
Represents a car entity in the database.

The CarEntity class is a JPA entity representing a car record in the database. It contains the basic properties of a car, such as brand, model, price, speed, and color, as well as the components associated with the car.

The entity uses a many-to-many relationship with the ComponentEntity class, and it supports cascading operations for persisting and merging associated components.

The class is mapped to the cars table, with a unique constraint on the combination of the brand and model columns to ensure uniqueness of each car model.
